               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183210180106"></xptr>PETER EVANS. I am a Norwegian <rs id="t18321018-260-viclabel1471" type="occupation">sailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321018-260-victim2230 t18321018-260-viclabel1471"></join>. On the 21st of October I was in <placeName id="t18321018-260-crimeloc1472">Ratcliff-highway</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18321018-260-crimeloc1472" type="placeName" value="Ratcliff-highway"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18321018-260-crimeloc1472" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321018-260-off1468 t18321018-260-crimeloc1472"></join>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321018-260-off1470 t18321018-260-crimeloc1472"></join>, and saw Watson - she was at a door; I went in with her, and went to bed with her - I had paid her 3s.; she then went away - I then missed my tobacco-pouch, my purse, one crown, and one half-crown from my lefthand waistcoat pocket; I did not see Parkinson.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321018-260-person2233">
                  JOHN 
                  MELVILLE
               <interp inst="t18321018-260-person2233" type="surname" value="MELVILLE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-260-person2233" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-260-person2233" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable K 63). I heard the prosecutor call Police! I went down; Watson was gone: I knew where she lived - I went and found her at her own house; I accused her of robbing the man- she said she had not taken any thing from him, and all the money she had in the world was one halfpenny - I asked her where her old man was, meaning Parkinson; I looked out of the window, and saw him outside - I got him in, searched, and found on him this little hammer, a crown-piece, and a half-crown: while I was doing that Watson ran off - I pursued and took her, and while I did that the serjeant searched Parkinson further, and found on him this purse and this pouch.</p>
               <p>PETER EVANS. This is my purse.</p>
               <p>Watson's Defence. I was sitting by my fire, he came to the door and asked if he might come in, and stay there; a woman came in - he sent for half a pint of gin, and a pot of porter; he said all he had was 7s. 6d., and a few halfpence - he gave me that; I took it to a woman to take care of for me; she gave it to Parkinson.</p>
               <p>Parkinson's Defence. I received it from another woman to take care of.</p>
               <p>WATSON - <rs id="t18321018-260-verdict1473" type="verdictDescription">
